Hey @briwa, I noticed the `ParamsSerializerOptions` type does not include the `serialize` prop.
The type should be aligned in the `index.d.ts` file.

Note: In v1.x, the `ParamsSerializerOptions` interface is defined like this: 

```
export interface ParamsSerializerOptions extends SerializerOptions {
  encode?: ParamEncoder;
  serialize?: CustomParamsSerializer;
}
```

Using the spread operator (`{...reducedDescriptors, [name]: ret || descriptor}`) in each iteration creates a new object every time, resulting in O(n²) performance instead of O(n). For objects with many properties, this could significantly impact performance.

Consider keeping the direct assignment approach but using `Object.defineProperty()` instead:
```javascript
forEach(descriptors, (descriptor, name) => {
  let ret;
  if ((ret = reducer(descriptor, name, obj)) !== false) {
    Object.defineProperty(reducedDescriptors, name, {
      value: ret || descriptor,
      writable: true,
      enumerable: true,
      configurable: true
    });
  }
});
```

This maintains both frozen prototype compatibility and optimal performance.
```suggestion
