The condition `!validProxyAuth` is redundant in the `else if` branch. Since this is an `else if`, we already know that `!validProxyAuth` must be true (because the `if` condition was false). The check can be simplified to:

```javascript
if (validProxyAuth) {
  proxy.auth = (proxy.auth.username || '') + ':' + (proxy.auth.password || '');
} else if (typeof proxy.auth === 'object') {
  throw new AxiosError('Invalid proxy authorization', AxiosError.ERR_BAD_OPTION, { proxy });
}
```

This makes the code clearer and follows the DRY principle.
